There are a lot of reasons for the high rate of divorce in Egyptian societies, such as cultural attitudes, economic hardships, and expectations. Cultural expectations can be defined as the standards that are set by the society to meet a certain standard.

Moderate eastern societies are regulated by their cultures, as they are strong and well observe their religions. This also consists of arranged marriage. Faith and religion have a strong history in this culture. Men follow traditions in female equality, and the women staying in the domestic domain and the men working family finances (Gods and Myths of Northern Europe, pg. 273).

Muslims view marriage as a strong union on a deeper level as opposed to a ritual and a social custom. Women are basically treated with respect. However, when they become submissive and the wife cooks and cleans for the family, they have gained respect. And when they hold a respectable position in the family, they have North Idaho this respect 3 then gained respect from society and they get praised.

Egyptian women are forced to adapt to their husband’s background and culture because they are male- dominated and live in societies that discriminate against women.
